==English==

===Verb===

{{en-infl-reg-other-e|delous|e|}}


#To remove [[lice]].  
#:''A [[veterinarian]] could delouse your dog''
#([[idiomatic]]) to apply [[insecticide|insecticides]] or repellants in order to be sure that no lice or other parasites are present.
#:''During the Korean Conflict, US soldiers were deloused with DDT upon entering basic training.''
#(Computer [[Jargon]]) to remove [[malicious]] software such as viruses, trojans, spyware, or worms.
#:''A deloused computer may no longer be considered trustworthy.''